'''Anthony P. Russo''' wrote the short story ''[[Blaze of Glory (short story)|Blaze of Glory]]'' for the ''[[Tales from the Empire]]'' anthology. Russo wrote [[Fanon|fan fiction]] ''Star Wars'' stories in high school "long before it was considered cool." Russo's first published short story appeared in ''Aboriginal Science Fiction'' magazine. He devoted development to the [[Live-Action Adventures|''Star Wars Live Action Roleplaying System'']] and was reportedly finishing his first full-length novel by the time ''Tales from the Empire'' was published in [[1997]].

